    <briefdescription>
<para>Filtering options, used when resizing images to sample original pixels. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1SamplingMode" kindref="compound">SamplingMode</ref> controls how pixels in an input image are sampled and combined to generate each pixel of a destination image during a scaling.</para>
<para>NoFilter and Box modes do not guarantee that the output pixel array exactly matches the rectangle specified by the desired dimensions and <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1FittingMode" kindref="compound">FittingMode</ref>, but all other filter modes do if the desired dimensions are <computeroutput>&lt;=</computeroutput> the raw dimensions of the input image file. @SINCE_2_5.14 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
